President Obama congratulates Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos on being awarded the Nobel Peace Prize for his efforts in bringing peace to Colombia. The President applauds Santos' courageous leadership and acknowledges the resilience of the Colombian people in turning away from a long-running war. The United States will continue to support Colombia through the Peace Colombia initiative, which aims to reinforce security, reintegrate former combatants into society, and promote opportunity and the rule of law. While there is still work to be done, the President believes that the award is a sign of progress and recognition for the positive changes happening in Colombia.